既不崇刚，乃以柔为强。虽以刚为强，乃以柔为强。既不崇刚，乃以柔为强。

This passage is a famous quote from the Chinese classic "Tao Te Ching" by Lao Tzu. It is often translated as:

"Adapt to the situation and you will find success;
Use your own strength and you will be weak;
Be weak and you will find success;
Be strong and you will be weak;
Be weak and you will find success;
Be strong and you will find success.

The meaning of this passage is that one should adapt to the situation and use their own strength and weakness to find success. It is not about being weak or strong in a physical sense, but rather about being flexible and adaptable in one's approach to life. The passage suggests that by being open to change and embracing one's own limitations, one can find success and achieve their goals.</s>
